          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p/>
              <p>Single folio on paper; Shelfmark: HC.MS.03182; Qurʾānic Text: Q  65:8-67:23; Lines per page: 26; Dimensions: 160 x 141 mm (with mounting:  244 x 168 mm); Script style: Maġribī micrography; Estimated date of production: 13th–15th centuries; Provenance: Muslim Iberia (al-Andalus).</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>The use of paper and the deliberately archaising script point towards a late medieval date. Yellow dots mark the <hi rend="italic">hamza </hi>above or below <hi rend="italic">alif</hi>. The symbols of <hi rend="italic">sukūn </hi>and <hi rend="italic">tašdīd </hi>are traced in blue, in contrast with all the other vocalisation marks, which are in red.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p/>
              <p/>
              <p>The frame shows floral ornamentation typical for Iranian provenance. On the left side <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/66/vers/10/handschrift/1381/bildversion/1">of the frame of the verso page</ref>  is an owner stamp and a note written in Persian (running vertically)  stating that manuscript is the "writing of Imām Ḥusain, martyr of the  desert of Karbala" (  خط امام حسين شهيد  دشت كربلا رضي الله عنه  ) . </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Image <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/65/vers/8/handschrift/1381/bildversion/1">1 of the</ref> <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/65/vers/8/handschrift/1381/bildversion/1">recto page </ref>has only the text of the manuscript, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/65/vers/8/handschrift/1381/bildversion/2">image 2 of the recto page</ref>  shows the manuscript in its frame. Image 1 of the <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/66/vers/10/handschrift/1381/bildversion/1">verso page</ref> has the text of the manuscript, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/66/vers/10/handschrift/1381/bildversion/2">image 2 of the verso page</ref> shows the manuscript in its frame. </p>
              <p> </p>
            </summary>
